      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i was watching the evening news report on the recent border policy changes and i noticed something weird. every time they mention certain \"humanitarian\" sectors, the anchor does this specific micro-nod and the lighting shifts slightly more towards blue. it's not random. i think the mainstream media is using these rhythmic cues to signal certain directives to their people. can u look into the pattern of how they frame the 'border crisis' vs 'humanitarian aid'? i feel like there's a hidden script here for their followers.",
